# Per-Dockerfile dockerignore for museum-web prod build.
# Docker BuildKit picks `<dockerfile>.dockerignore` over the root `.dockerignore`
# when present (cf. https://docs.docker.com/build/concepts/context/#dockerignore-files).
#
# Why this file exists : the root /.dockerignore (committed 2026-05-17 commit
# `20161545`) excludes `museum-web/` to keep the BACKEND build context small.
# Without this override, the web build (which also uses repo-root context to
# reach `packages/musaium-shared/`) couldn't COPY museum-web/package.json
# → build failed with "/museum-web/pnpm-lock.yaml not found"
# (cf. CI web run 25987665015).
#
# Pattern : every Dockerfile that uses repo-root context MUST ship its own
# co-located .dockerignore.

# ─── Heavy / unrelated apps ────────────────────────────────────────────────
museum-frontend
museum-backend
design-system
docs
infra
team-reports

# ─── Tool / VCS / agent state ──────────────────────────────────────────────
.git
.github
.husky
.claude
.cursor
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store

# ─── Per-pkg build artefacts + caches (musaium-shared/dist IS shipped) ─────
**/node_modules
**/coverage
**/.cache
**/.turbo
**/.next
**/dist-server
**/.expo
**/.expo-shared
**/.eas
**/build
**/.test-dist
**/.stryker-tmp
**/.stryker-run

# ─── Env / secrets ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
!**/.env.production.example
!**/.env.host-mode

# ─── Logs / debug ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
**/*.log
**/npm-debug.log
**/yarn-debug.log
**/yarn-error.log

# ─── Misc ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
**/*.tsbuildinfo
**/Thumbs.db
